    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub! ‚ù§Ô∏è Today, I am going to show you. How to make text bold in react js with code example. Use inline styles to bold specific‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! ‚ù§Ô∏è</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you. How to make text bold in react js with code example.</p>\n<p>Use inline styles to bold specific text in React.js, e.g. <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;span style={{fontWeight: 'bold'}}>aGuideHub&lt;/span></code>. The bold font will only be applied to the element to which it was added and its children.</p>\n<p>Let‚Äôs look at the following example to understand how it basically works:</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">APP.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">App</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>p style<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token literal-property property\">fontSize</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'2rem'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        Welcome To<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>span style<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token literal-property property\">fontWeight</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'bold'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> aGuideHub<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>span<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token operator\">!</span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  \n  <span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>We used <code class=\"language-text\">inline</code> styles to bold some text in an element.</p>\n<p>The first set of curly braces in the <code class=\"language-text\">inline</code> style marks the beginning of an expression, and the second set of curly braces is the object containing styles and values.</p>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">bold</code> font is only going to be applied to the <code class=\"language-text\">span</code> element.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Step to Run Application:</em></strong> Run the application using the following <code class=\"language-text\">command</code> from the root directory of the project:</p>\n<h3>npm start</h3>\n<p><strong><em>Output:</em></strong> Now open your browser and go to <code class=\"language-text\">http://localhost:3000/,</code> you will see the following output:</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/535152be698a5ee5a2572c1819d61a92/38f6f/text-bold.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 51.26582278481012%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React , Text, Bold\"\n        title=\"React , Text, Bold\"\n        src=\"/static/535152be698a5ee5a2572c1819d61a92/828fb/text-bold.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/535152be698a5ee5a2572c1819d61a92/ff44c/text-bold.jpg 158w,\n/static/535152be698a5ee5a2572c1819d61a92/a6688/text-bold.jpg 315w,\n/static/535152be698a5ee5a2572c1819d61a92/828fb/text-bold.jpg 630w,\n/static/535152be698a5ee5a2572c1819d61a92/0ede0/text-bold.jpg 945w,\n/static/535152be698a5ee5a2572c1819d61a92/3ac88/text-bold.jpg 1260w,\n/static/535152be698a5ee5a2572c1819d61a92/38f6f/text-bold.jpg 1366w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to make text bold in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"June 01, 2022","description":"Example of make text bold in React with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to check if a string starts with a substring in golang?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/how-to-check-if-a-string-starts-with-a-substring-in-golang/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to make text clickable in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/how-to-make-text-clickable-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/how-to-make-text-bold-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/how-to-check-if-a-string-starts-with-a-substring-in-golang/","nextSlug":"/blog/how-to-make-text-clickable-in-react-js/"}},
